 <nfraprado@collabora.com>
Date: Mon, 8 Jun 2026 11:48:50 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] sleep: Don't fallback to suspend if hibernate failed with
 ECANCELED
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

If hibernate in suspend-then-hibernate failed with -ECANCELED, that
means it was intentionally cancelled, so don't fallback to suspend, let
the system wake up.

Signed-off-by: Nícolas F. R. A. Prado <nfraprado@collabora.com>
---
 src/sleep/sleep.c | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/sleep/sleep.c b/src/sleep/sleep.c
index 181bb4ccefc5..4632332cce5f 100644
--- a/src/sleep/sleep.c
+++ b/src/sleep/sleep.c
@@ -506,6 +506,11 @@ static int execute_s2h(const SleepConfig *sleep_config) {
         log_debug("Attempting to hibernate");
         r = execute(sleep_config, SLEEP_HIBERNATE, NULL);
         if (r < 0) {
+                if (r == -ECANCELED) {
+                        log_notice("Hibernate intentionally cancelled, won't attempt to suspend.");
+                        return r;
+                }
+
                 log_notice("Couldn't hibernate, will try to suspend again.");
 
                 r = execute(sleep_config, SLEEP_SUSPEND, "suspend-after-failed-hibernate");
-- 
